caption.p:
Bed bug preference (five females, five males) for a paper tent impregnated with essential oil constituents (1%) aged for 24 h vs. a tent impregnated with acetone. After a 14-h test period, the number of insects resting on any of the treatment harborages or wandering on the arena was recorded. * Significant differences between control and EOC-treated tents (
   p < 0.05; 
   N = 6).
